$interpreted: Miranda: Wah~ so many colors...quite different from the mountains in the East Alliance.
Miranda: If Master was here, no doubt he would shake his head and recite some poem...
Miranda: Ah, yes...that one that Master always recites would be perfect right now...

Miranda: Let me think...
I know a...bank...whereon the flies do blow...
where time and space...something...grows.
Miranda: No, no, no that's not right. Can't remember~
Miranda: The literature from the East is so wordy...there's no way a foreigner like me can learn...
Miranda: ...Who's there?
Miranda: Come out! I'm gonna countdown from three. Three...
Miranda: One!
Miranda: Strange...I certainly felt like...ah!
Miranda: Panthers!? The residents of Whistlewood valley!
Miranda: Perfect, just who I'm looking for!
Fatima: ......
Miranda: Hey, who goes on the attack right away!?
Miranda: If you'd like to compete, we'll get to it. At least let me state why I'm here...
Miranda: Alright, we'll see who's skills reign supreme!
Miranda: Quite fast...impressive.
Fatima: ......
Fatima: ......
Panther Officer: Who are you? Why are you intruding on our territory?
Miranda: Ah, finally. Someone is willing to speak with me.
Miranda: Good day, my name is Miranda. I'm from the East Alliance!
Fatima: ......
Young Panther: The East Alliance? That's very far...
Panther Officer: Our ancestors left the East Alliance many generations ago. Why have you come to us?
Miranda: Don't misunderstand me. I wasn't sent by them~
Miranda: I'm entering the East Alliance Martial Arts Tourney. In order to qualify, I'd like to borrow the Holy Talisman.
Panther Officer: Holy Talisman...?
Miranda: Master said that the great tribes of the alliance all have such an artifact. May I borrow it? I'll bring it right back, I promise.
Young Panther: ...Captain, do you know what she's talking about?
Panther Officer: No. I've never heard of it.
Panther Officer: What is this nonsense? What is this trickery? Just like those malevolent humans from the past...
Miranda: Not. At. All! My master is the Grandmaster of the Wolf Tribe. He can verify what I've said!
Panther Officer: The Wolf Beasts? And, where is your master?
Miranda: We were walking together, but he'll be a few days late.
Miranda: ...The more I think about it, the more worried I get. Is Master Yan-Bo even still alive...?
Panther Officer: I have no idea what you're talking about...what should we do captain?
Fatima: ......
Panther Officer: Hey, human. The captain will allow you into our territory. Whether you live or die depends on the matriarch.
Miranda: Thank you, captain...what's your name?
Fatima: ......
Miranda: Hey, can your captain speak?
Young Panther: Rubbish! Better watch yourself before Fatima slaughters you!
Miranda: Oooh~Fatima, I see. What a beautiful name!
